Rating: 4
These were fantastic--they tasted a lot like falafel without the fried crust. I found that the bulghur needed 2 cups of water to soften all the way. (The recipe should specify fine grain bulghur, as mine was medium to coarse.) After processing the mixture in the food processor, I put it into a bowl and chilled the entire thing for 2 hours. It was then very easy to shape into patties. Preheat the grill pan well before adding the oil and the burgers won't stick or fall apart. Don't be tempted to forego the lime mayo--it really makes this dish! If you're vegan, you can find acceptable versions of vegan mayo at Whole Foods.

