Rating: 3
I altered the recipe slightly, doubled it, and grilled the burgers. They were good, not amazing, I plan to make them on a regular basis in the future. After reading reviews I decided to add 1 egg and 1/2 cup of bread crumbs to the mixture (4 servings). This REALLY changes the consistency of the mixture and you can pureé the entire thing much more finely. After forming the patties (which were fairly large) I dropped them in a bowl of bread crumbs so they wouldn't be so sticky. I then chilled them overnight and then froze them, letting them thaw about 15-25 minutes in the open before I put them on the grill. Despite all the reviews these burgers stayed together amazingly on the grill sheet, they were even more cohesive than some hamburgers I've eaten. If I were doing this recipe again I would probably add some of the lime zest to the patty mixture and a touch of cinnamon maybe 1/2 a teaspoon to a teaspoon, depending on how adventurous I was feeling. Also, tweaking the sauce is a very good idea, I added some chipotle for flavor and paprika for color next time I'll probably add chives and someone suggested sriracha sauce. Anyway, good recipe, not perfect, but definitely going to make it again.

