I made this for a picnic and didn't have a food processor. I used a pastry cutter to mash up the beans and nuts and even though they were chunky, they were fabulous. I also added extra cumin, coriander, soy sauce to taste, a touch of salt, a clove of pressed garlic and the secret ingredient...the juice of about one lime or to taste. YUM!

Rating: 4
Made a lovely girl's lunch item with some rose on the deck! We subbed roasted pumpkin seeds for the walnuts and topped with sauteed mushrooms, had a watercress salad on the side and made extra lime mayo to dip some oven fries in-divine! These will be made en-masse and vacu-sealed for later use.

